item.title: Ender 3 Satsana Dual Fan with BL Touch
item.description:
I made 3 changes to the Satsana Dual Fan Fanduct.

  1. I removed a small piece on the left side because it hit the X limit switch and triggered 3 mm earlier.
  2. The distance between fan & L Touch was too small. I moved it 1mm further to the left.
  3. The outlet opening was rotated 5 degrees further down so that it no longer blows against the silicone buffer.

item.title: Nextion 2.8 Simagic GT1 Box
item.description:
Box cover modification from https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:1497062

Box cover has extension to fit SIMAGIC GT1 wheel base and 70mm hub.

The box files are available from original source https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:1497062

Note that to fit the current 2.8 Nextion display required the bottom original internal posts to be modified (removed) and the nextion display corners glued in place (I used automotive goop). You will understand when you get there..

I used double sided tape to hold the usb ttl adapter to the bottom of the wheel base. I then secured the coiled usb cable to hub with velcro.

Simhub provides the display.

Let me know if you make use of it.

item.title: Speaker adapter for Subaru Forester - Adattatore speaker per Subaru Forester
item.description:
I designed this speaker adapter to mount a pair of hertz speakers for a friend on his Subaru Forester (model year 1997). The speakers are 165mm wide and he bought them from amazon (Hertz dcx 165). The adapter can be mounted on the front doors panel using the original screws and to link the speaker to the adapter you have to use the original screws plus one because it has four holes. To prevent vibration on the panel, it's recommended to put a little layer of insulation material on the adapter's surface that is in contact with the door's panel (as the original speaker mount). The adapter has two grooves, to pass the wires; and the higher depth of the speaker isn't a problem for the door glass (when you pull it down), it doesn't touch it.

Ho progettato questo adattatore per montare un paio di speaker Hertz sulla Subaru Forester di un amico (modello anno 1997). Gli speaker hanno diametro 165mm e sono stati comprati su amazon (Hertz dcx 165). L'adattatore può essere montato sul pannello porta (portiere anteriori) utilizzando le tre viti originali e per montare lo speaker all'adattatore si possono usare le viti originali, più una dato che la cassa ha un foro di fissaggio in più. Per evitare vibrazioni e rumori, si consiglia di mettere un leggero strato di materiale isolante sulla superficie dell'adattatore in contatto con il pannello porta (come nel porta-speaker originale). L'adattatore presenta due scanalature per far passare i cavi; e la profondità maggiore dello speaker non è un problema per il vetro (quando viene abbassato), i due non si toccano.

item.title: Vinyl Record Drying Rack (or for anything else
item.description:
This is simple to print, 2 part rack (you'll need to print 11 of the arms if you want one in every slot) and one of the bases. I designed it for drying Vinyl records after wet cleaning them. It supports them surprising well for how small it is. There are small grooves in the base to keep the records centered and keep them from rolling off.
Obviously you could use it for just about anything you want to organize in a rack (perfect for letters, envelopes etc.
At 100% scale its 2.5" x 6.5" long, and and 2.5" tall, the spacing between each arm is about 3/8" . You could easily scale this up in your slicer program to fit your needs.
Flat print everything, no supports needed,
I had to give the corners of the support arms (where they fit down in the holes) a scraping with a blade to get them to slot down in the holes at first, but then they fit down in snugly with no glue needed, and wiggle free.
I put a small dimple on the top of each arm, to keep contact with my records to a minimum. To ensure this part doesn't scratch my records, I gave each dimple a drop of paint to create a smooth surface.

item.title: SIKU 4010 FAUN Lift Gear Replacement
item.description:
This is a replacement lift gear for the SIKU 4010 heavy crane. It works for you as long as you have the metal cylinders that attach to the crane. This set consists of two parts:

Part A) two connected hydraulic tubes
Part B) toothed rod to determine lift height

Print both parts flat at 40% infill. Regular PLA will suffice. Part A requires supports with "Touch Platform Only" option.

You will need to disassemble the model by opening the rivets on the underside of the crane in order to make this repair.

item.title: Split in 2 pieces for shorter print beds (Remix Can Crusher Base)
item.description:
I couldn't get the original version of this to fit in my printer, so I made it into two pieces with attachments. I also added holes for screws along the middle of the back, because I plan to mount it on a joist. They should fit a #8 wood screw.

You'll need to turn the top piece upside down to print. Still need supports for the pin holes & screw holes.

The middle screw hole goes through both pieces for added strength, but I still glued both pieces together to make sure it's as strong as possible.

I realize there was another remix for shorter print beds, but I couldn't get it to print on an angle.
